What are Animal By-products and Why is Demand Increasing?
Animal by-products (ABPs) are entire animal bodies, body parts, products of animal origin, or other materials obtained from animals that are not intended for human consumption. These materials are processed into valuable products such as meat and bone meal, feather meal, blood meal, animal fats, collagen, gelatin, and specialty proteins that serve a wide range of industrial applications.

Rather than being discarded as waste, animal by-products are converted into high-value ingredients through modern rendering, hydrolysis, and extraction technologies. These products provide cost-effective protein sources for livestock nutrition, premium ingredients for pet food, renewable feedstocks for biodiesel production, and specialty materials for pharmaceutical and cosmetic industries, making them an essential component of sustainable resource management.

